The paper deals with the Hospital Residents problem, which is a well-studied problem in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also introduces the notion of popularity for the HRLQ problem, which involves voting and preference lists, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithmic aspect of the paper, which involves computing a maximum cardinality matching, falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses stability, which is a concept commonly studied in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with a specific problem instance with lower quotas, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
